            "id": "a5981a55088040af9194f",
            "questionText": "A bowling ball, which can be modeled as a solid sphere, has a mass of $!$M = 7\\,\\text{kg}$!$ and a radius of $!$R = 0.1\\,\\text{m}$!$. It rolls without slipping down a bowling lane with a linear velocity of its center of mass being $!$v = 4\\,\\text{m/s}$!$. What is the total kinetic energy of the bowling ball as it travels down the lane?",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "6c4018f05696406fbf6d1",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by identifying the correct expression for the total kinetic energy of a rolling object. Please select the correct formula.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "36fae90c-82f8-4597-9669-7f280c300fc6"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$KE_{total} = \\frac{1}{2} Mv^2 + \\frac{1}{2} I \\omega^2$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$KE_{total} = Mv^2 + I \\omega^2$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$KE_{total} = \\frac{1}{2} I \\omega^2$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "f889fd25e6334bf3aef4c",
                    "stepText": "Great. Now, identify the correct moment of inertia for a solid sphere. Choose the appropriate formula.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "f6586b7d-c0fe-4287-91e9-f20de7e236bd"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$I = \\frac{2}{5}MR^2$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$I = \\frac{1}{2}MR^2$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$I = MR^2$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "6f240e02422d44f4a89f2",
                    "stepText": "Excellent. For rolling without slipping, the angular velocity is related to the linear velocity. Which relation correctly represents this condition? Please select the correct option.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "daaa4850-76fd-458c-99ae-480cec59b41f"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$v = \\omega R$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\omega = vR$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$v = \\frac{\\omega}{R}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "615a288815bc4de78c5e5",
                    "stepText": "Now, calculate the translational kinetic energy using the formula $!$\\frac{1}{2}Mv^2$!$. Use the given mass and linear velocity.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
